    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28,
                            1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 258.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Markell’s No. 408 of the
                        13th ultimo, reporting that he has been advised by the Government of Brazil
                        that the export duties on skins improperly collected by the State of Bahia
                        will be returned to the exporters on presentation of their claims to the
                        treasury of the State, and that similar action will be recommended by the
                        governor of Pernambuco to the State legislature.</p>
                <pb facs="0140" n="32" xml:id="pg_32"/>
                <p>You will express to the Brazilian Government our satisfaction at the action
                        taken by the State of Bahia, and our hope that that of the State of
                        Pernambuco will be equally satisfactory.</p>
                <p>The consuls at Bahia and Pernambuco will be advised.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alyey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
